This paper deals with computer vision tasks such as motion trajectory segmentation and multi-target tracking, which are typically categorized under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a joint graphical model for point trajectories and object detections, which involves machine learning techniques such as optimization and probabilistic modeling, which are commonly associated with machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of object detection and tracking, which are related to robotics (cs.RO) and multimedia (cs.MM).
